              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17916111061205736935">I received a free copy of this book through Goodread&apos;s Giveaways.<br/><br/>This book was fantastic. I finished it in 1 day, I just couldn&apos;t put it down. From almost the first page I was hooked.<br/><br/>The book started with the funeral of a female solder killed in action and didn&apos;t stop.<br/><br/>I felt the secondary story with Leah and Cal Conners wasn&apos;t necessary but did make for a nice diversion from the intensity of the main story on occasions. Although the secondary plot does set up for a sequel nicely, without taking </span>
  <span id="freeText17916111061205736935" style="display:none">I received a free copy of this book through Goodread's Giveaways.<br /><br />This book was fantastic. I finished it in 1 day, I just couldn't put it down. From almost the first page I was hooked.<br /><br />The book started with the funeral of a female solder killed in action and didn't stop.<br /><br />I felt the secondary story with Leah and Cal Conners wasn't necessary but did make for a nice diversion from the intensity of the main story on occasions. Although the secondary plot does set up for a sequel nicely, without taking away from the overall ending of the novel.<br /><br />I was pleasantly surprised by this book and highly recommend it.</span>
